Independent schools in Scotland have maintained a record of academic excellence, a trend which continued in 2018 with new excellent test results reinforced by collective and individual achievement in sport, art, music and other community activities.
With over 30,000 pupils across Scotland, these schools, represented by the Scottish Council of Independent Schools (SCIS), strive to provide the best level of service to pupils and their parents.
Independent schools work to prepare their students for higher education, their chosen careers and their place as citizens of the world.
