Now, languages as subjects are organised alongside science, technology, engineering and mathematics in the curricula of independent schools and other schools.
A 2014 survey by the UK Commission for Employment and Skills found that 17% of the difficulties employers face in recruiting candidates are linked to insufficient language skills.
