The Global Citizen Festival, which was first held in 2012, is an extension of the Global Poverty Project, an international advocacy group that hopes to eradicate poverty by increasing the number of people who actively fight it.
In order to receive a free ticket to the event (unless you are willing to pay for a VIP ticket), spectators had to complete a series of tasks, or actions, such as volunteering, sending an email to a world leader, making a phone call, or doing any other useful effort to raise awareness about the fight against poverty.
