 With the support of the UK government, donors, national governments and Global Citizens like you, we can make the social injustice of malnutrition a footnote in history , said Tracey Ullman, ambassador of The Power of Nutrition programme, to the crowd at a concert in London in April 2018.
The group also said that following the launch of more than 5,000 actions to call on the UK to improve maternal and child nutrition, the government has announced funding for a project, The Power of Nutrition, which will benefit 5 million women and children through nutrition interventions.
In response to one of the most frequently asked questions on his website, what makes you think that it is possible to end extreme poverty?
Global Citizen said:  The road to get there will be long and difficult, sometimes we will fall and fail.
